**What I have to do for the assignment**


Pick a dataset with a numerical value I want to predict (the target).
Load the dataset and look at it to understand the columns and basic structure.
Clean the data by handling missing values and fixing any obvious issues.
Separate the target column from the rest of the features.
Identify which columns are numerical and which are categorical.
Convert categorical columns into numerical format so models can use them (this is where OneHotEncoder comes in).
Scale or normalize numerical features so they are on similar ranges.
Create any useful new features that might help prediction.
Split the data into a training set and a test set.
Set up a pipeline that combines all preprocessing steps with a model.
Train a simple baseline regression model on the training data.
Evaluate each model using the test set to see how well it predicts.
Compare model results and choose the best-performing one.
Analyze which features were most important for the best model.
Write a short summary explaining what worked, what didn’t, and which features mattered most.
